  "_coverage_actual_pct": 100.0,
  "_note": "Per-entry _verification_status records sourcing. cross_references.* populated at X.D.1 back-fill (currently all null). The 13-47 00 00 umbrella entry is excluded from entries[] as the parent_category header. The secondary mirror exposes three level-2 sub-trees under 13-47: Worship Spaces (13-47 11), Ceremonial Spaces (13-47 13), Procession Spaces (13-47 15), and Death Spaces (13-47 17). Worship Spaces is the largest sub-tree, with 16 level-4 leaf codes covering elements and rooms found in Christian, Islamic, and Jewish worship settings (Chapel, Mihrab, Shrine, Sanctuary, Confessional Space, Ark, Bimah, Tabernacle, Pulpit, Choir Loft, and three orientation/reflection spaces). Ceremonial Spaces includes Marriage Sanctuary, Baptistery, Circumcision Space, and Cathedra. Procession Spaces (13-47 15 00) appears in the mirror without further leaf codes — it is included as a level-3 stub with _verification_status: mirror_sourced. Death Spaces (13-47 17) includes Morgue (13-47 17 13) and its child Morgue Compartment (13-47 17 13 11), and Grave Space (13-47 17 17). ifc_space_type=EXTERNAL applied to Grave Space as an open-air interment area per IfcSpaceTypeEnum (ISO 16739); all other entries are INTERNAL enclosed spaces. The entry_count_target of 10 is exceeded because the mirror coverage of 13-47 is dense across all four sub-trees. Future Sprint Y back-fill from the canonical OCCS PDF (CSI license) will raise _verification_status from mirror_sourced to occs_verified and may expose additional leaf codes under Procession Spaces (13-47 15) and Death Spaces (13-47 17).",
